# SSH (Secure Shell)

## Overview

SSH is a secure protocol used for remote administration of Linux systems.

It encrypts all communication between the client and server.

---

## Components

- SSH Client
- SSH Server

---

## Common Commands

```bash
which ssh
systemctl status ssh
systemctl is-enabled ssh
ssh localhost
```

---

## Common Uses

- Remote login
- Server management
- Secure command execution
- Secure file transfer

---

## Key Takeaways

- SSH replaces Telnet.
- SSH uses encryption.
- OpenSSH is the default implementation on Ubuntu.
